      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="VariableName-small">Line-of-Centers</text><text style="font-weight:bold; font-style:italic;">:</text><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal;"> (shown as a thick </text><text style="font-weight:bold; font-style:normal; color:#008000;">green</text><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal;"> line) is the Line that is between the center points of two gears in a Gear-Pair. The </text><text styleclass="VariableName-small">Line-of-Centers</text><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal;"> may be stationary (simple, compound gears) or rotate (epicyclic, planetary, differential gears) relative to the mechanism frame.</text></para>
